I'm torn whether this is a 5 star game or a 1 star game. fundamentally, it's a dopamine machine with some alright gacha characters. The gameplay leaves some depth to be desired. Especially the monotony on which enemies you are fighting. Also, I would like my response to losing to be more "how can I change my strategy" rather than " how many resources do I need to get." Just give me the illusion of strategy and choice. I'm still having an ok time playing the game, especially in shorter bursts.

AFK Arena, in its current form, isn't easy to get into, but it has a lot of charm, varied game modes, and interesting lore. Finding a good mentor through a guild, of which there are plenty, will also make progression much smoother, and take much of the stress away from learning how to play. If you take your time, and treat this as a casual experience, you may find yourself enjoying your stay in Esperia!
